The agency who announced this on Thursday via their various social media platforms, said that the suspects were dragged to court by the agency’s Kaduna Zonal Command. The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has arraigned a former Vice Chancellor of the Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria, Professor Ibrahim Garba, and Ibrahim Shehu Usman, the former bursar of the school before Kaduna State High Court on an eight-count charge bordering on theft and money laundering to the tune of over N1billion. The agency who announced this on Thursday via their various social media platforms, said that the suspects were dragged to court by the agency’s Kaduna Zonal Command. “Ex- ABU VC, Bursar Arraigned for N1bn Fraud “Professor Ibrahim Garba, and Ibrahim Shehu Usman, former Vice Chancellor and Bursar respectively of the Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria were today arraigned before Justice A. A Bello of the Kaduna State High Court. “The arraignment followed months of discreet investigation triggered by a petition accusing the duo of diverting monies meant for the renovation of the popular Kongo Conference Hotel, Zaria. “The investigation established that over N1billion was allegedly stolen from different accounts of the institution by the defendants and diverted into their private accounts,” the anti-corruption body stated. Ex- ABU VC, Bursar Arraigned for N1bn Fraud Professor Ibrahim Garba, and Ibrahim Shehu Usman, former Vice Chancellor and Bursar respectively of the Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria were today arraigned before Justice A. A Bello of the Kaduna State High Court... pic.twitter.com/Vo1rEQGAdB — EFCC Nigeria (@officialEFCC) January 12, 2023